Pre-Game Insights: Both teams want to bounce back from losses in their respective opening games.

Historically, Ukraine has had the upper hand, winning both meetings in the inaugural Nations League campaign.
Ukraine’s track record in head-to-head games and their capacity to perform away from home help to position them as modest favourites.
The Czech Republic has been inconsistent in recent matches, struggling both in international tournaments and the Nations League.
Ukraine has managed two wins in their last five games, although their form has been inconsistent.
Ukraine has a slight edge in recent meetings, with two victories in the Nations League campaign of 2018-19.
The Czech Republic will look to bounce back in this crucial UEFA Nations League fixture with a strong and balanced lineup.
Ukraine, led by coach Sergiy Rebrov, is expected to field a competitive team, combining a mix of youth and experience.
Injuries to key Ukrainian players like Artem Dovbyk and Mykhaylo Mudryk may impact their attacking options.
